-- Bank of America to pay $9.3 billion to settle mortgage bond claims
-- 
-- Wed Mar 26, 2014 04:39PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, March 26 (Reuters) - Bank of America <BAC.N> will pay $9.3 billion to Fannie Mae <FNMA.OB> and Freddie Mac <FMCC.OB> to settle claims that it sold them faulty mortgage-backed securities during the housing bubble, a U.S. regulator said on Wednesday.   (Reporting By Margaret Chadbourn)  ((margaret.chadbourn@thomsonreuters.com)(+1 202 354 5806)(Reuters Messaging: margaret.chadbourn.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: BANKOFAMERICA SETTLEMENT/FHFA

